{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βάσις</b> [ᾰ], εως, ἡ, <br /> (βαίνω) <b>stepping, step,</b> and collectively, <b>steps,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 36, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 8, etc.: _metaphorically_, ἡσύχῳ φρενῶν βάσει 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 452 (Lyric poetry); οὐκ ἔχων β. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>power to step,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 691 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τροχῶν βάσεις the <b>rolling</b> of the wheels, the <b>rolling</b> wheels, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “El.” 718 \">Refs</a>]; ἀρβύλης β. the <b>print</b> of the sandal, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 532; ποίμναις τήνδ᾽ ἐπεμπίπτει βάσιν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 42. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>measured stepor movement,</b> β. χορείας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 968, compare 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 1.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: hence, <b>rhythmical</b> or <b>metrical movement,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 399e, “Lg.” 670d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in Rhet., <b>rhythmical close</b> of a sentence, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ ἰδεῶν” 1.6, +others\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>clause forming transition from</b> πρότασις <b>to</b> ἀπόδοσις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Inv.” 1.5 \">Refs</a>]: and in Metric, <b>metrical unit, monometer,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1263b35, “Metaphorical” 1087b36, 7th c.AD: Hephaestio Grammaticus 11, 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor “Prolegomena ad Hephaestionis Euchiridion” 3, Mar. Vict. p.47.3 K., etc. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>order, sequence,</b> θέσις καὶ β. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.10U. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>that with which one steps, a foot,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 92a, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 750a4; ποδῶν β. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 837 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θηλύπους β. their women's <b>feet,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “IA” 421 \">Refs</a>]; β. δίχηλος, of the ostrich, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 3.28.3: _absolutely_, αἱ βάσεις 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.226, NT.Act.3.7; σφὶγξ εἶχε β. λέοντος 2nd c.AD: Apollodorus Damascenus Mechanicus 3.5.8 \">NT+1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>leg,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.3.5; βάσεων ἀποκοπαί 2nd c.AD: Diogenes Oenoandensis Epicureus 39. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>that whereon one stands, base, pedestal,</b> [κρατῆρος] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 119 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of statues, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “OGI” 705.6, etc.; τρία ἔργα.. ἐπὶ μιᾶς β. 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 14.1.14, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Philops.” 19; λεβήτων 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.88.5 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; of an engine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus “Belopoeica” 88.1, +others \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; of a column, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLond.” 3.755v6 (4th c.AD): in Medicine texts, τοῦ ἐγκεφάλου 3rd c.BC: Herophilus Medicus cited in “Placita Philosophorum” 4.5.4, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pericles” 6; τραχήλου [prev. author] “Pyrrh.” 34; κοῖλαι βλεφάρων ἰοτυπεῖς βάσιες “Anthologia Graeca” 5.86 (2nd-3rd c.AD: Rufinus Epigrammaticus); αἱ ἐν ὀφθαλμοῖς β. 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.27, compare 2nd c.AD: Archigenes Medicus cited in 6th c.AD: Aëtius Medicus 16.101(91) \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; of the heart, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “de Usu Partium” 6.13; ἐπανόρθωσις τὴν τοῦ κενουμένου βάσιν ἀναπληροῦσα [prev. author] 1.474 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>foundation, basement,</b> ῥίζα πάντων καὶ β. ἁ γᾶ ἐρήρεισται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 97e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so, of the soil, πεδίων σπορίμα β. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hymnus ad Isim” 162. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> Geometry texts, <b>base</b> of a solid or plane figure, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 55b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Priora” 41b15, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [κώνου] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 155; πυραμίδος 4th c.BC: Speusippus Philosophus cited in “Theologumena Arithmeticae” 63. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>position, fixedness,</b> opposed to φορά, <i>etymology</i> of βέβαιος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 437a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> Astrology texts, ={ὡροσκόπος}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 88.6, 4th c.AD: Paulus Alexandrinus Astrologus “T.” 2, “Catalogus Codicum Astrologorum” 8(4).132. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0939","accentedUnicode":"βάσις","shortDef":"foot","mediumDef":"<i>primarily</i> <b>a step; the foot,</b> <ref='Act.3.7'>Acts 3:7</ref>*","stepGloss":"foot","stepTransliteration":"basis","count":1,"_es_Definition":"pie (del cuerpo)","_zh_tw_Definition":"腳 (徒 3:7)","_zh_Definition":"脚 (徒 3:7)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"bàn chân, một bước.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"